rounds.event: King George V of the United Kingdom dies. His eldest son succeeds to the throne, becoming Edward VIII. The title Prince of Wales is not used for another 22 years.
deaths: George V of the United Kingdom

rounds.event: In the United States, Martin Luther King Jr. Day is celebrated as a federal holiday for the first time.
births: Kevin Parker, Australian singer, songwriter, musician, and producer

rounds.event: Barack Obama is inaugurated as the 44th President of the United States of America, becoming the first African-American President of the United States.
In the United States, the National Negro Network is established with 40 charter member radio stations.
births: Mohammad Dawran, Afghan aviator and military officer
Alison Seabeck, English lawyer and politician
deaths: Fred Root, English cricketer and umpire

rounds.event: Amílcar Cabral, leader of the independence movement in Guinea-Bissau and Cape Verde, is assassinated in Conakry, Guinea.
births: Stephen Crabb, Scottish-Welsh politician, Secretary of State for Wales
deaths: Lorenz Böhler, Austrian physician and surgeon
Amílcar Cabral, Guinea Bissauan-Cape Verdian engineer and politician
